ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a really fabulous course. You will be impressed by Professor Bubula. You will never regret taking this.
I would highly recommend the course to anyone interested in International Trade/Economics
Yes. Really interesting topics but the pace is very fast and material is fairly difficult if you haven't taken Econ before
It's useful for those who want to work in international policy.

Yes, definetly I recommend this class to other students. But, in my opinin, in order to enhance the effectiveness of this class, I recommend them to take this course after or at the same time as the intermediate level of macroeconomics course.
A logic exercise. Recommended for students outside of IDE.
Economics 702 offers broad concepts of international trade and macroeconomics.Yes I would recommend this course to another student.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have learned a lot about international trade and economics from this course. It was helpful to understand the international conflict and policy.
Yes, the difficulty and the pace are very nice for a master level class. Not too fast and not too slow. I learned a lot from the class.
This lecture gave me the basic knowledge to read more advance level paper about the international macroeconomics, such as the determinant of exchange rate etc.
Clearifies and extends my previous knowlegde. I appreciate that the professor is constantly providing us some ideas for our thesis throughout the term.
Concepts learned from this course connects nicely with other core courses in my program such as macroeconomics.
